“It looks like [@Janey Farina|https://neurio.slack.com/team/U072S2NEK3R] created a story to remind us to add rudimentary support for the LED to unblock board level testing. It's not scheduled for any sprint, not sure when we'll have time to get to it. Maybe Janey has a better idea of this. As for full LED/UI support there's no tickets for that, I have a firmware roadmap meeting later today I'll see if we can figure out when it might get done then”

Erich Beyer  [11:58 AM|https://neurio.slack.com/archives/D06S1UJ9DE3/p1721761082627869]


In the BMU test spec you wrote a long time ago, you had a test for the cabinet switch with a description: "Toggle the cabinet switch to verify BMU turns on. Toggle switch again to turn off BMU. "

Is this actually the way that the BMU works? It seems to me that the switch only turns on the bmu, not turns it off



Tanner Whipps  [12:18 PM|https://neurio.slack.com/archives/D06S1UJ9DE3/p1721762286920219]

Correct, this is how the R1 system works and from what I understand is how the R2 system will work as well. I just confirmed with Arnav that the cabinet switch functionality is not yet implemented in the code.

He said it should be merged in with the next release candidate

column1: Debug Penguin Issue When Connected to Manta
column29:
Penguin 2.1 serial communication is not working when connected to manta proto8. I tried with 2 different penguin 2.1 and both do not work with manta. 

Checked the harness and all pins are one to one (manta to penguin) so harness configuration is correct. 

I used 24V, GND, CANHI, and CANLO from the can bus to power penguin and I was able to see serial comms. 

Next check is to remove the reset connection from manta to penguin to make sure manta is not sending reset commands to penguin constantly.
